# Data Fetching & Mutations

## Data Retrieval — Server Components Only

Always fetch data in React Server Components. Never fetch data on the client side (no `useEffect` + `fetch`, no SWR/React Query calling API routes for initial data).

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — Server Component
export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  const decks = await db.select().from(decksTable).where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));
  return <DeckList decks={decks} />;
}

// ❌ BAD — Client-side fetching
"use client";
useEffect(() => { fetch("/api/decks").then(...) }, []);
```

## Mutations — Server Actions Only

All inserts, updates, and deletes must be implemented as Next.js Server Actions. Never use API routes (`/app/api/`) for mutations.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — Server Action
"use server";
export async function createDeck(data: CreateDeckInput) { ... }

// ❌ BAD — API route mutation
// POST /api/decks/route.ts
```

## Validation — Zod Required

All data passed to server actions must be:
1. Validated with a Zod schema
2. Typed with a TypeScript type derived from that schema (use `z.infer<>`)
3. Never typed as `FormData`

```ts
import { z } from "zod";

const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  description: z.string().max(500).optional(),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeck(data: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = createDeckSchema.safeParse(data);
  if (!parsed.success) throw new Error("Invalid input");
  // proceed with parsed.data
}
```
